The '''France national under-18 football team''' is the national under-18 football team of [[France]] and is controlled by the [[French Football Federation]]. The team serves as a feeder team to the [[France national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] as its matches aren't competitive. The under-18 team only participate in [[Exhibition match|friendly matches]] and tournaments, such as the SBS Cup and the [[TaÃ§a do AtlÃ¢ntico]].

The 2011â12 international under-18 campaign will begin on 23 August 2011 and current coach of the under-20 team is [[Francis Smerecki]], a former football player, notably with [[Le Mans Union Club 72|Le Mans]] and [[Limoges FC|Limoges]]. Prior to coaching for the French Football Federation, he had domestic coaching tenures at [[USL Dunkerque]], [[En Avant de Guingamp]], and [[AS Nancy]]. In the 2010â11 season, Smericki coached the [[France national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] to victory at the [[2010 UEFA European Under-19 Football Championship]] and led the [[France national under-20 football team|under-20 team]] to a fourth place finish at the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. The current captain of the under-18 team is [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] defender [[RaphaÃ«l Calvet]].

